## 4. Purpose of this public repository

The purpose of this repository is to make the Grimoire system understandable.

It exists so that people can:
- study the technical direction,
- understand how spell authoring is intended to work,
- follow the development of the system behind Grand Wizard Tournament,
- and propose spell ideas or feedback in a structured and reviewable form.

This repository is not an unrestricted open collaboration space. It is a curated public-facing development repository.

## 5. Spell proposals and submissions

This repository may be used as a place for spell ideas, spell structure proposals, feedback, or other curated submissions.

The project owner may review, reject, ignore, refine, respond to, or internally reinterpret any submission at sole discretion.

Nothing in this repository creates any obligation to:
- accept a proposal,
- merge a contribution,
- include an idea in the game,
- credit a suggestion publicly,
- compensate a submitter,
- or adopt submitted material in any form.

If code or content is ever considered for official inclusion, separate written terms or a contributor agreement may be required before acceptance.

